title: Cieciorka, Pomeranian Voivodeship
text:
Cieciorka () is a <a href="village">village</a> in the administrative district of <a href="Gmina%20Kaliska">Gmina Kaliska</a>, within <a href="Starogard%20County">Starogard County</a>, <a href="Pomeranian%20Voivodeship">Pomeranian Voivodeship</a>, in northern Poland. It lies approximately north of <a href="Kaliska%2C%20Gmina%20Kaliska">Kaliska</a>, west of <a href="Starogard%20Gda%C5%84ski">Starogard Gdański</a>, and south-west of the regional capital <a href="Gda%C5%84sk">Gdańsk</a>.
For details of the history of the region, see "<a href="History%20of%20Pomerania">History of Pomerania</a>".
The village has a population of 518.
